  "prompt": "What happens when you withdraw linkedin invitation?",
  "response": "When you withdraw a LinkedIn invitation:\n\n1. The invitation is immediately cancelled and removed from the recipient's pending invitations\n\n2. The person will not be notified that you withdrew the invitation\n\n3. You can send them another invitation later if you want\n\n4. The action does not negatively impact your LinkedIn network or profile\n\n5. If you've previously withdrawn several invitations to the same person, LinkedIn might temporarily restrict your ability to send them new connection requests\n\nSo withdrawing an invitation is a discreet process without any significant consequences or notifications to the other person.",
